Two people died and 19 others were injured on Tuesday evening after a bus belonging to Kenya Bus Service rammed into six other vehicles along Haile Selassie Avenue in Nairobi. John Majiwa from St John Ambulance said 18 casualties were rushed to Nairobi Hospital and another to Kenyatta National Hospital.  The KBS bus that caused the accident. /COURTESY The bus, which was headed to the city centre, lost control after seemingly losing its breaks, hit a pedestrian and knocked the other vehicles. A school bus belonging to Loreto Convent was among those involved in the accident. Click here for the latest political news           